    <name>
				<text>1.2.5.6 Simplify indices</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise <br></p>
<p>Write each of the following expressions with a single index:</p>

<ol class="HELM_parts">
<li>\( (x^{@a2@})^{@a3@}= \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</li>
<li>\(x^{@b2@}x^{@b1@}= \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</li>
<li>\(\dfrac{x^{@c2@}}{x^{@c1@}}= \) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]</li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<ol class="HELM_parts">
  <li><p>Use the third law of indices:</p>
    <p>\((x^{@a2@})^{@a3@}= x^{{@a2@}\times{@a3@}}={@ta1n@}\).</p>
  </li>

  <li><p>Use the first law of indices:</p>
    <p>\(x^{@b2@}x^{@b1@} = x^{{@b2@}+{@b1@}}={@ta2@}\).</p>
    </li>

   <li><p>Use the second law of indices:</p>
    <p>\(\dfrac{x^{@c2@}}{x^{@c1@}}=x^{{@c2@}-{@c1@}}={@ta3@}\).</p>
   </li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
